30#define SHADER_ENTRY_NAME @"main0"
31class ContextMtl;
32
33struct ProgramArgumentBufferEncoderMtl
34{
35 void reset(ContextMtl *contextMtl);
36
37 mtl::AutoObjCPtr<id<MTLArgumentEncoder>> metalArgBufferEncoder;
38 mtl::BufferPool bufferPool;
39};
40
41// Represents a specialized shader variant. For example, a shader variant with fragment coverage
42// mask enabled and a shader variant without.
43struct ProgramShaderObjVariantMtl
44{
45 void reset(ContextMtl *contextMtl);
46
47 mtl::AutoObjCPtr<id<MTLFunction>> metalShader;
48 // UBO's argument buffer encoder. Used when number of UBOs used exceeds number of allowed
49 // discrete slots, and thus needs to encode all into one argument buffer.
50 ProgramArgumentBufferEncoderMtl uboArgBufferEncoder;
51
52 // Store reference to the TranslatedShaderInfo to easy querying mapped textures/UBO/XFB
53 // bindings.
54 const mtl::TranslatedShaderInfo *translatedSrcInfo;
55};
56
57class ProgramMtl : public ProgramImpl, public mtl::RenderPipelineCacheSpecializeShaderFactory
58{
59 public:
60 ProgramMtl(const gl::ProgramState &state);
61 ~ProgramMtl() override;
62
63 void destroy(const gl::Context *context) override;
64
65 std::unique_ptr<LinkEvent> load(const gl::Context *context,
66 gl::BinaryInputStream *stream,
67 gl::InfoLog &infoLog) override;
68 void save(const gl::Context *context, gl::BinaryOutputStream *stream) override;
69 void setBinaryRetrievableHint(bool retrievable) override;
70 void setSeparable(bool separable) override;
71
72 std::unique_ptr<LinkEvent> link(const gl::Context *context,
73 const gl::ProgramLinkedResources &resources,
74 gl::InfoLog &infoLog,
75 const gl::ProgramMergedVaryings &mergedVaryings) override;
76 GLboolean validate(const gl::Caps &caps, gl::InfoLog *infoLog) override;
77
78 void setUniform1fv(GLint location, GLsizei count, const GLfloat *v) override;
79 void setUniform2fv(GLint location, GLsizei count, const GLfloat *v) override;
80 void setUniform3fv(GLint location, GLsizei count, const GLfloat *v) override;
81 void setUniform4fv(GLint location, GLsizei count, const GLfloat *v) override;
82 void setUniform1iv(GLint location, GLsizei count, const GLint *v) override;
83 void setUniform2iv(GLint location, GLsizei count, const GLint *v) override;
84 void setUniform3iv(GLint location, GLsizei count, const GLint *v) override;
85 void setUniform4iv(GLint location, GLsizei count, const GLint *v) override;
86 void setUniform1uiv(GLint location, GLsizei count, const GLuint *v) override;
87 void setUniform2uiv(GLint location, GLsizei count, const GLuint *v) override;
88 void setUniform3uiv(GLint location, GLsizei count, const GLuint *v) override;
89 void setUniform4uiv(GLint location, GLsizei count, const GLuint *v) override;
90 void setUniformMatrix2fv(GLint location,
91 GLsizei count,
92 GLboolean transpose,
93 const GLfloat *value) override;
94 void setUniformMatrix3fv(GLint location,
95 GLsizei count,
96 GLboolean transpose,
97 const GLfloat *value) override;
98 void setUniformMatrix4fv(GLint location,
99 GLsizei count,
100 GLboolean transpose,
101 const GLfloat *value) override;
102 void setUniformMatrix2x3fv(GLint location,
103 GLsizei count,
104 GLboolean transpose,
105 const GLfloat *value) override;
106 void setUniformMatrix3x2fv(GLint location,
107 GLsizei count,
108 GLboolean transpose,
109 const GLfloat *value) override;
110 void setUniformMatrix2x4fv(GLint location,
111 GLsizei count,
112 GLboolean transpose,
113 const GLfloat *value) override;
114 void setUniformMatrix4x2fv(GLint location,
115 GLsizei count,
116 GLboolean transpose,
117 const GLfloat *value) override;
118 void setUniformMatrix3x4fv(GLint location,
119 GLsizei count,
120 GLboolean transpose,
121 const GLfloat *value) override;
122 void setUniformMatrix4x3fv(GLint location,
123 GLsizei count,
124 GLboolean transpose,
125 const GLfloat *value) override;
126
127 void getUniformfv(const gl::Context *context, GLint location, GLfloat *params) const override;
128 void getUniformiv(const gl::Context *context, GLint location, GLint *params) const override;
129 void getUniformuiv(const gl::Context *context, GLint location, GLuint *params) const override;
130
131 // Override mtl::RenderPipelineCacheSpecializeShaderFactory
132 angle::Result getSpecializedShader(mtl::Context *context,
133 gl::ShaderType shaderType,
134 const mtl::RenderPipelineDesc &renderPipelineDesc,
135 id<MTLFunction> *shaderOut) override;
136 bool hasSpecializedShader(gl::ShaderType shaderType,
137 const mtl::RenderPipelineDesc &renderPipelineDesc) override;
138
139 angle::Result createMslShaderLib(mtl::Context *context,
140 gl::ShaderType shaderType,
141 gl::InfoLog &infoLog,
142 mtl::TranslatedShaderInfo *translatedMslInfo,
143 NSDictionary<NSString*, NSObject*> * subtitutionDictionary = @{});
144 // Calls this before drawing, changedPipelineDesc is passed when vertex attributes desc and/or
145 // shader program changed.
146 angle::Result setupDraw(const gl::Context *glContext,
147 mtl::RenderCommandEncoder *cmdEncoder,
148 const mtl::RenderPipelineDesc &pipelineDesc,
149 bool pipelineDescChanged,
150 bool forceTexturesSetting,
151 bool uniformBuffersDirty,
152 bool transformFeedbackDraw);
153
154 std::array<uint32_t, mtl::kMaxShaderXFBs> getXfbBindings() const { return mXfbBindings; }
155 std::string getTranslatedShaderSource(const gl::ShaderType shaderType) const { return mMslShaderTranslateInfo[shaderType].metalShaderSource; }
156 bool hasFlatAttribute();
157
158 mtl::RenderPipelineCache *mMetalXfbRenderPipelineCache;
159
160 private:
161 template <int cols, int rows>
162 void setUniformMatrixfv(GLint location,
163 GLsizei count,
164 GLboolean transpose,
165 const GLfloat *value);
166 template <class T>
167 void getUniformImpl(GLint location, T *v, GLenum entryPointType) const;
168
169 template <typename T>
170 void setUniformImpl(GLint location, GLsizei count, const T *v, GLenum entryPointType);
171
172 angle::Result initDefaultUniformBlocks(const gl::Context *glContext);
173 angle::Result resizeDefaultUniformBlocksMemory(const gl::Context *glContext,
174 const gl::ShaderMap<size_t> &requiredBufferSize);
175 void saveDefaultUniformBlocksInfo(gl::BinaryOutputStream *stream);
176 angle::Result loadDefaultUniformBlocksInfo(const gl::Context *glContext,
177 gl::BinaryInputStream *stream);
178
179 angle::Result commitUniforms(ContextMtl *context, mtl::RenderCommandEncoder *cmdEncoder);
180 angle::Result updateTextures(const gl::Context *glContext,
181 mtl::RenderCommandEncoder *cmdEncoder,
182 bool forceUpdate);
183
184 angle::Result updateUniformBuffers(ContextMtl *context,
185 mtl::RenderCommandEncoder *cmdEncoder,
186 const mtl::RenderPipelineDesc &pipelineDesc);
187 angle::Result legalizeUniformBufferOffsets(ContextMtl *context,

197 gl::ShaderType shaderType);

199 void reset(ContextMtl *context);
200
201 void saveTranslatedShaders(gl::BinaryOutputStream *stream);
202 void loadTranslatedShaders(gl::BinaryInputStream *stream);

204 void saveShaderInternalInfo(gl::BinaryOutputStream *stream);
205 void loadShaderInternalInfo(gl::BinaryInputStream *stream);

227 mtl::BufferPool * getBufferPool(ContextMtl * context);
228
229 bool programHasFlatAttributes() const;
230 // State for the default uniform blocks.
231 struct DefaultUniformBlock final : private angle::NonCopyable
232 {
233 DefaultUniformBlock();
234 ~DefaultUniformBlock();
235
236 // Shadow copies of the shader uniform data.
237 angle::MemoryBuffer uniformData;
238
239 // Since the default blocks are laid out in std140, this tells us where to write on a call
240 // to a setUniform method. They are arranged in uniform location order.
241 std::vector<sh::BlockMemberInfo> uniformLayout;
242 };
243
244 gl::ShaderBitSet mDefaultUniformBlocksDirty;
245 gl::ShaderBitSet mSamplerBindingsDirty;
246 gl::ShaderMap<DefaultUniformBlock> mDefaultUniformBlocks;
247
248 // Translated metal shaders:
249 gl::ShaderMap<mtl::TranslatedShaderInfo> mMslShaderTranslateInfo;
250
251 // Translated metal version for transform feedback only vertex shader:
252 // - Metal doesn't allow vertex shader to write to both buffers and to stage output
253 // (gl_Position). Need a special version of vertex shader that only writes to transform feedback
254 // buffers.
255 mtl::TranslatedShaderInfo mMslXfbOnlyVertexShaderInfo;
256
257 // Compiled native shader object variants:
258 // - Vertex shader: One with emulated rasterization discard, one with true rasterization
259 // discard, one without.
260 mtl::RenderPipelineRasterStateMap<ProgramShaderObjVariantMtl> mVertexShaderVariants;
261 // - Fragment shader: One with sample coverage mask enabled, one with it disabled.
262 std::array<ProgramShaderObjVariantMtl, 2> mFragmentShaderVariants;
263
264 // Cached references of current shader variants.
265 gl::ShaderMap<ProgramShaderObjVariantMtl *> mCurrentShaderVariants;
266
267 ShaderMapInterfaceVariableInfoMap mVariableInfoMap;
268 // Scratch data:
269 // Legalized buffers and their offsets. For example, uniform buffer's offset=1 is not a valid
270 // offset, it will be converted to legal offset and the result is stored in this array.
271 std::vector<std::pair<mtl::BufferRef, uint32_t>> mLegalizedOffsetedUniformBuffers;
272 // Stores the render stages usage of each uniform buffer. Only used if the buffers are encoded
273 // into an argument buffer.
274 std::vector<uint32_t> mArgumentBufferRenderStageUsages;
275
276 uint32_t mShadowCompareModes[mtl::kMaxShaderSamplers] = {0};
277
278 mtl::RenderPipelineCache mMetalRenderPipelineCache;
279 std::array<uint32_t, mtl::kMaxShaderXFBs> mXfbBindings;
280 mtl::BufferPool * mAuxBufferPool;
281 bool mHasFlatAttribute;
282};
